   <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol , 1867, p. 1: </mads:note>
   <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly:  "Hegesianax of Alexandra,Lived under Antiochus III of Antioch (222-187 BC) and became the king's ‘friend’ (phílos, 
      SH 464) when he gave him his poetry. ...Grammarian, author of the work ‘On the Style of Democritus’ and ‘On the Poetic Style’ as well as
      astronomical-mythological poetry (Phainómena, SH fr. 465-467; in total five hexameters have been passed down, but the allocation is uncertain; 
      ... H. is the oldest known author of the ‘Trojan histories’ (Trōïká), perhaps also cited under the name Historíai.......
      with further bibliographical references) that were published under the fictitious name Cephalon (or Cephalium) of Gergis....."
      Fornaro, Sotera (Sassari).Hegesianax." Brill’s New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. 
      Brill Online, 2013. Reference. Tufts University Library. </mads:note>
